=== Converting predicates to numeric functions ===

In some settings it is natural to consider primitive recursive functions that take as inputs tuples that mix numbers with truth values (that is formula_52 for true and formula_12 for false), or that produce truth values as outputs. This can be accomplished by identifying the truth values with numbers in any fixed manner. For example, it is common to identify the truth value formula_52 with the number formula_55 and the truth value formula_12 with the number formula_13. Once this identification has been made, the characteristic function of a set formula_58, which always returns formula_55 or formula_13, can be viewed as a predicate that tells whether a number is in the set formula_58. Such an identification of predicates with numeric functions will be assumed for the remainder of this article.

