<doc id="24830" wikidata="Q352798" url="?curid=24830" title="Peisistratus (disambiguation)">
<text>Peisistratus was a tyrant of Athens, Greece, three different times between 561 and 528 BC.

Peisistratus, Peisistratos or Pisistratus may also refer to:
* Peisistratus (&quot;Odyssey&quot;), son of Nestor who appears in &quot;The Odyssey&quot;
* Peisistratos of Lapithos, 4th century BC
* Peisistratus of Orchomenus, king of Arcadian Orchomenus during the Peloponnesian War
* Pisistratus the Younger, r. 522–521 BC, an annual archon of Athens</text><links>
